      "rationale": "The primary validation QoIs — NIH and wall shear stress distribution — are the direct inputs to the hemolysis power-law model used to compute RH. Pressure rise and velocity field serve as secondary QoIs confirming overall flow physics fidelity. The linkage between validation QoIs and the COU decision criterion is explicitly documented in the credibility assessment plan."
