      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table was prepared comparing CFD boundary conditions against experimentally measured conditions for each of the five operating points. Inlet turbulence intensity (5% assumed in CFD vs. estimated 4–6% in experiments) and outlet pressure boundary condition (atmospheric vs. measured back-pressure within ±100 Pa) were identified as minor deviations. Sensitivity runs confirmed that these deviations produce less than 1% change in NIH predictions."
